{"id": "1431718571972624474", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 0, "author_id": "337981494641295360", "author_name": "omenatyyppi", "author_bot": false, "content": "how are you plaing salv? That team comp is more than capable of beating chapter6", "timestamp": "2025-10-25T18:58:27.603000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1431718614909587618", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 19, "author_id": "393585313618067456", "author_name": "katesthio", "author_bot": false, "content": "Daff team is you’re second weakest team, due to how this team wants high invest. I would recommend running them on Wave 1 or Wave 2 cause of this nature. Wave 4’s consecutive boss fights are tough with a Daff team until you have a throughly built Daff team. I believe you are playing right(from everything in 1, 2, 3), but it’s simply your Daff team is too weak(Daff needs more invest) to run a pure “boss” rush Wave(4). To add on, Wave 4’s nature(boss rush) doesn’t allow you to stack your “Skulk Reaver” 3 cost by every kill using it, giving it 25% Dmg Amp. Boss Rush is ideally done with a OE Daff, since then she can burst much more for how Boss Rush wants you to nuke boss to boss as fast as possible. Lastly, I would say you lack Potraits to amp your team before you even get to your first boss. Reason is this week is Chaos Ring rotation, so Daff team has 0 Potraits at the start, while Tawil team would have 3 portraits at the VERY BEGINNING of the run(headstart basically).\n\nE3 vs OE burst turn for Endgame\nNo Potraits from Ring(Versus Tawil Team Having 3 Potraits from Chaos Ring)", "timestamp": "2025-10-25T18:58:37.840000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["196755044685709313"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1431626543825948682", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
